# SDK Project Structure

Use [sdk_scaffolding](https://github.com/TernStay/sdk_scaffolding) as the starting point for new SDKs. The reference implementation is [turnstay_api_admin_sdk](https://github.com/TernStay/turnstay_api_admin_sdk).

## Desired Layout

```
{sdk_name}/
├── {sdk_name}/
│   ├── client.py
│   ├── client_utils.py
│   ├── auth_utils.py      # optional, for complex auth
│   ├── settings.py
│   ├── __about__.py
│   └── schemas/
│       ├── requests.py
│       ├── responses.py
│       ├── types.py
│       └── {endpoint}/
│           └── {endpoint}.py
├── tests/
│   ├── test_client_*.py
│   └── fixtures/
├── run_sdk.py
└── pyproject.toml
```

## Adding a New Endpoint

1. Create schema module: Params/GetParams, Response, Request/GetRequest
2. Add Client method: kwargs → Request → `execute(request)`
3. Add to `run_sdk.py`
4. Add to tests
5. Do **not** add branching, retries, or custom logic to the Client method
6. Mirror naming and structure of existing endpoints

## Version Bump

After modifying the SDK, bump the version in `pyproject.toml` or `__about__.py` (when using hatch dynamic version).

## Quick Reference

| Task | Action |
|------|--------|
| New endpoint | Schema (Params, Response, Request) → Client method → run_sdk.py → tests |
| HTTP logic | Put in client_utils.py |
| Auth helpers | Put in auth_utils.py if complex |
| Client method | kwargs → Request → `execute(request)` only |
| Tests | One file per method; fixtures + mocks |
| Release | Bump version in pyproject.toml / __about__.py |
